{
  "stem": "27340.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "The danger of a German invasion was always still with us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And so when I met this commanding officer, a colonel who'd been a colonel in his own right in the first World War and was too old now to serve in this current war, a very charming fellow, he told me to jump into the car.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And he drove me to one or two of these anti-aircraft batteries.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he showed me how they operated.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "He showed me the control mechanisms, the control room, as it were.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He showed me where the ammunition was being kept.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And on the way back, he said, young man, I hope you appreciate that you and I are the only two people who know about the exact disposition of our armaments.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And I thought what an ridiculous irony that on the one hand, I was being kicked out of the Air Training Corps because I was a security risk, and here, albeit it was only the Home Guard, nevertheless [LAUGHS] he opened up his entire secrets if we can call it that to a guy who was such a security risk.",
      "word_count": 60
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Anyway, I had a very interesting time in the Home Guard.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I was seconded to the battalion intelligence section, not because I was intelligent but because I spoke German as well.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And that was considered to be useful.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "In case we could take German prisoners, I'd be able to interrogate them and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that's-- of course, the Home Guard was stood down long before the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I've got a really nice illuminated, sort of, document signed by HM the King thanking me, like everybody else, for their valiant services in the defense of the realm.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's an illuminated thing.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
